The paper deals with unsupervised learning and segmentation of hyperspectral images, which is a problem in computer vision (CV). The proposed method involves a diffusion-inspired labeling process, which is a common technique in machine learning (ML) and specifically in unsupervised learning (LG). The paper also discusses the use of partial least squares regression (PLSR) and active learning, which are both techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) and information retrieval (IR). Finally, the paper involves optimization of parameters, which is a common task in neural networks (NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.IR, and cs.NE.
